Rxh2+ 28. Kg1 c5 29. Ra8 Rxa8 30. Bxa8 Rh4 31. Bc6 Rb4 32. a4 Rb2 33. c4 Kg7
34. Rd3 Ra2 35. Kf1 Kg6 {[#] White is doomed to a passive defence.} 36. Re3 h5
37. Re2 Ra3 38. Rd2 h4 39. Ke2 Bf4 40. Rd3 Ra2+ 41. Kd1 Kf6 42. Rf3 Be5 43. Rd3
Ke7 $1 {Important plan to transfer the king and cut white's bishop.} 44. Rd2
Ra3 45. Ke2 Bc3 46. Rd3 Ra2+ 47. Kd1 Bd4 48. Rh3 Bf6 49. Re3+ Be5 50. Rd3 Kd8
51. Rd2 Ra1+ 52. Ke2 Kc7 $1 {After this move the bishop will be completely out
of play.} 53. Bb5 Bf4 54. Rc2 $2 {Losing move,} ({It was necessary to stay on
the d-file with} 54. Rd1) 54... Ra3 {Now Ficher took control of the third rank.
} 55. Rb2 Be5 56. Rd2 Rg3 57. Kd1 f4 {Parma resigned since after f4-f3 the
h-pawn will promote.} 0-1


